Amy Martin is an American rower who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics. She attended Oregon State University, where she began rowing in 1992. She earned a silver medal in the 1999 World Championships, and a bronze medal in 1998. Martin was a member of the U.S. women's eight rowing team that competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics. The U.S. team came in 6th place.
Martin now owns and operates Frontier Outdoors, a worldwide adventure videography company.

